<SECOND>AM-Missing Sailor,0145</SECOND>
<HEAD>Search Ends for Sailor Missing from U.S. Destroyer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANAMA, Bahrain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Navy officials said Sunday they have
suspended their search for an American sailor who apparently fell
overboard last week as his destroyer was patrolling the Persian
Gulf.
   They identified the missing man as Brian S. Voltz, 20, of
Springfield, Mo., a postal clerk third class aboard the USS Conolly.
   A search of the gulf 50 miles northeast of Dubai was called off
late Friday, according to Navy spokesman Joseph Bartlett.
   The crew man was reported missing from the 7,810-ton ship during
routine patrol late Wednesday. The search was launched after three
checks of the ship.
   The Conolly, with a crew of about 325, has operated with the
Navy's gulf-based Middle East Force since mid-April and is
scheduled to leave next month for home port at Norfolk, Va.
