<HEAD>Text of Death Threat Against U.S. Marine</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Israel-Abduction, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The following is the text of the
statement issued Sunday by the Organization of the Oppressed on
Earth threatening to kill U.S. Marine Lt. Col. William R. Higgins
if Israel did not release abducted Shiite Moslem cleric Abdul Karim
Obeid.
   It was translated from Arabic by The Associated Press.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   In the Name of God, the Merciful, the Compassionate,
   O sons of our Islamic nation,
   O free men and oppressed of the world,
   It appears that the Zionist government is persisting in its
terrorist and aggressive policy against Islam and the Moslems. A
screaming proof of this is the latest aggression carried out by the
army of the Israeli enemy in which struggler Sheik Abdul Karim
Obeid was abducted along with two brethren. Another son of the town
of Jibchit also was killed.
