<HEAD>Lightning Strikes at Ballpark; Three Hospitalized</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WICHITA, Kan. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A lightning strike at a softball park
Sunday injured three people, including a man who had been talking
on a telephone in a concession stand, authorities said.
   ``We think it struck the metal backstop behind the
ballplayers,'' said Capt. Robert Pippin of the Sedgwick County
Emergency Medical Service.
   Gary Cunningham, 33, Alan Wray, 27, and Grant Black, 27, were
listed in fair condition Sunday evening at St. Francis Regional
Medical Center, said Jo Wescott, a nursing supervisor. All three
are from Wichita.
   No one was directly hit by the lighting, but ``the impact and
disbursement of the energy knocked several people off their feet
and to the ground,'' said Alan Green, a paramedic with the Wichita
Fire Department. ``It took them a minute to realize what happened.''
   It was partly cloudy at the time of the strike.
